An RE has the following options to onboard a customer: 
(a) Face-to-face onboarding: 
• Visit to the branch/ office of the RE; 
• using e-KYC authentication (OTP as well as biometric based authentication); 
undertaking offline verification of proof of possession of Aadhaar Number; 
obtaining certified copy of the OVD or equivalent e-document thereof; 
undertaking ‘Digital KYC Process’, as per paragraph 16 of the MD on KYC.

The KYC policy shall include following four key elements: 
(a) Customer Acceptance Policy; 
(b) Risk Management; 
(c) Customer Identification Procedures (CIP); and 
(d) Monitoring of Transactions 
